Misuzu Oda

  • daughter of Sakunosuke & Ango [Sakaguchi] Oda
    • 7th oldest of her family; middle triplet of Toshiyuki Oda and Matsutarou Oda
  • girl, xenogender (nonbinary)
    • she/they/xe
  • bisexual
  • starts the series at 9 and ends at 16
  • born October 1st, 2005
  • Namesake: Misuzu Kaneko
  • Ability: Are You an Echo?
    • Ability Details: I haven't thought much about this Ability yet, but I have read the poem it's based off of, and I think it should probably have something to do with a person's "echoes," or images / "snapshots" so to speak, of them at an earlier point in time. Perhaps making them a separate entity from the person themselves, who knows.
  • Affiliation: she is one of only four of the Oda children within the Port Mafia, and is only there due to wanting to follow in her older brother, Takeshi Oda's, footsteps. She is a Trainee within the Port Mafia Junior Training Division.
  • Level at which I think about them: low
  • Brief Notes:
    • Despite her employment in the PM, Misuzu is a sunny person. She's a cutesy type for sure, which when coupled with her soft, quiet voice, eccentric and old-fashioned style of dress, and her overall nonthreatening demeanor, make it easy for her to trick people into believing she's far less dangerous than she actually is. Underneath her unassuming facade lies a penchant and passion for homicidal violence, and it's best that everyone around her - friends and family included - knows and remembers what she's capable of, for their own sakes.
